      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics model selection (turbulence closure, hemolysis constitutive law) justified by sensitivity analysis and literature survey for VAD conditions.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on prior pump literature. Hemolysis power-law constants from Giersiepen et al. are known to have limited range; sensitivity to alternative constants not quantified. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties defined with quantified uncertainty; Monte Carlo propagation completed.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on inlet flow rate and rotational speed. Blood viscosity uncertainty was not propagated; fixed nominal value used. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
